  "title": "ACMV Technician (Facilities Management)| Construction Industry",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our client offers a comprehensive facilities maintenance and technical infrastructure management, with consistent record of reliable performance</strong><br /><br />Job Description & Requirements</p><ul><li>Experience in ACMV, AHU, FCU, COOLING TOWER </li><li>Carry out all preventive and corrective maintenance for all ACMV systems in the building</li><li>Perform investigation, rectification works and update supervisor on the progress</li><li>Respond to all complaints promptly including part replacement</li><li>Perform regular maintenance at site </li><li>Undertake ad-hoc maintenance or repair tasks as assigned</li><li>Enforce and promote a strong safety culture during all maintenance activities</li><li>Ensure safe keeping of hand tools and maintain good house keeping</li><li>Any other duties as and when assigned</li><li>Comply with uniform dress code while working and maintain a neat and clean appearance while on the property at all times</li></ul><p>Requirements :</p><ul><li>BCA SEC(k) / coretrade in ACMV or mechanical trade preferred</li><li>Willing and able to work in healthcare division </li><li>Minimum 3 years in ACMV maintenance in building facilities</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Excellent WSH experience and behaviour </li><li>Transport allowance provided</li></ul><p>Work Shift : </p><p>Mondays to Fridays: 8am to 5pm</p><p>Alternate Saturdays: 8am to 12pm<br /></p><p>WHATSAPP US AT +65 6817 3075</p><p>Rachel Chua XinJie</p><p>EA Personnel Reg. No. R22107077</p><p>Equator Search Pte Ltd</p><p>(EA Licence No. 14C7203)</p><p>18 Boon Lay Way | #02-126 Tradehub 21 | Singapore 609966<br />We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. By submitting your application, you hereby give consent to Equator Search Pte Ltd (MOM Licence No 14C7203), for the collection, use and disclosure of the personal data in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA).</p>",
